### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = <paste_access_token_here>
@clientId = <paste_client_id_here>

### 1) Crear cliente
# @name createClient
POST {{baseUrl}}/client
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Construcciones García S.L.",
  "cif": "B87654321",
  "email": "contacto@garcia.com",
  "phone": "912345678",
  "address": {
    "street": "Calle Mayor",
    "number": "42",
    "postal": "28013",
    "city": "Madrid",
    "province": "Madrid"
  }
}

### 2) Listar clientes (con paginación y filtro por nombre)
GET {{baseUrl}}/client?page=1&limit=10&name=García&sort=-createdAt
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3) Obtener cliente concreto
GET {{baseUrl}}/client/{{clientId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4) Listar clientes archivados
GET {{baseUrl}}/client/archived
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5) Actualizar cliente
PUT {{baseUrl}}/client/{{clientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "phone": "666777888",
  "email": "nuevo@garcia.com"
}

### 6) Archivar cliente (soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/client/{{clientId}}?soft=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7) Borrar cliente permanentemente (hard delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/client/{{clientId}}?soft=false
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8) Restaurar cliente archivado
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/client/{{clientId}}/restore
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
